Text: It was a nice episode. I just didn't care for Melisandre using her shadow monster to reanimate Renly's corpse and using it to convince his soldiers to side with Stannis. Even in the book I thought it was a bit unbelievable! But oh my god that last scene with Cersei discovering Shae and chopping her head off to force Tyrion to leave her children alone was exactly how I imagined it! Too bad Sansa is going to be traumatized now. But as long as her madness drives her to stabbing Joffrey in the season finale I dont care. Spiller people complained I didnt put any spiler tags so there!
